				<td colspan="2"><span>Conaden,
<br />

<br />
I've done a LOT of LDoNs.  No small number of them were pickup groups.  I've grouped with lots of rangers.  I'm sorry to say that at least half of them were sub-par.  Some others were good.  A smaller number were VERY good.  About four that I remember were OUTSTANDING!  The four that I mention had many great things in common, and one specific thing (relating to this discussion) was that they were masters of ghetto-mezzing (root-parking).  I assumed that they had had to learn this skill when there was no other form of CC available to them in other pickup groups.
<br />

<br />
Basically, assuming they hadn't grouped with many bards, I had to tell each of them (nicely) that I would handle the CC duties.  Bard Mezz is much more predictable and stable than ghetto-mezzing (root parking).  After I told them this, they understood completely and were fine with it.
<br />

<br />
I am assuming that the ranger you were grouped with maybe kept thinking the mobs were root-parked and that shooting arrows at them would be &quot;ok&quot;, although this wouldn't really be all that great for his longevity (his arrow dps would take him high on the aggro list).  *shrug*.  Who knows?  Maybe he was just an arse.
<br />

<br />
I'm just suggesting that there might have been another reason for what he was doing.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
